@peekowang There's nothing fishy with the link, the red stuff is normal behavior; your browser is warning you that the site's certificate is verified by an untrusted authority. That's completely normal. Accept the certificate and you're on your way. If you don't like it, replace HTTPS with HTTP instead. But I highly recommend using HTTPS where available. The more awareness you have about security the better.
